Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells based on yttrium-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte and Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) electrode are prepared via phase-inversion and impregnation processes.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: The YSZ symmetrical electrolyte support is constructed using two porous frameworks and one thin-dense-membrane via phase-inversion combined with drip-coating techniques.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: SFM is infiltrated into the porous frameworks of the symmetric YSZ support to work as electrodes.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: Nanoscale Pr6O11 catalysts are further infiltrated into the electrodes to promote electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: The optimal loading of SFM and Pr6O11 are systematically investigated.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, with the optimal loading of SFM (12 wt%), the polarization resistance (R-p) for anode and cathode of the cell decrease to 0.19 and 0.10 Omega.cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: The maximum power density (MPD) achieves 301 mW.cm(-2) in H-2 at 800 degrees C. After loading Pr6O11, the R-p for anode and cathode further decrease by 47% to 0.10 Omega.cm(2) and by 80% to 0.021 Omega.cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: And the MPD improves by 51% to 455 mW.cm(-2) (at 800 degrees C).
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst

Sentencas: These results and analysis of distribution of relaxation times demonstrate that the introduction of Pr6O11 as bifunctional catalysts is a promising approach for simultaneously improving H-2 fuel oxidation and O-2 reduction activities.
Titulo: Enhancing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via infiltration of Pr6O11 bifunctional catalyst
